events.title: FBINET to UNET File Upload
events.description: An email notification indicates files related to the Epstein investigation were uploaded from the FBI's network (FBINET) to another network (UNET).

keyFacts: The document is an email dated March 9, 2020, regarding the upload of files from FBINET to UNET.
The uploaded file is named '90A-NY-3151227ipsteinn Email_regarding_meeting_with_Signet.msg', indicating it is an email concerning a meeting with 'Signet'.
The communication originates from the FBI New York Field Office Violent Crimes Task Force, showing active FBI involvement in the Epstein case at that time.
The file naming convention '90A-NY-3151227ipsteinn' suggests it is part of a specific FBI case file related to Jeffrey Epstein.
The document demonstrates internal FBI procedural communication regarding the handling of case evidence or information.
